Sentencas: In this work, solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC's) are fabricated with linear-compositionally graded anode functional layers (CGAFL) using a computer-controlled compound aerosol deposition (CCAD) system.
Titulo: Compositional control of continuously graded anode functional layer

Sentencas: Cells with different CGAFL thicknesses (30 urn and 50 um) are prepared with a continuous compositionally graded interface deposited between the electrolyte and anode support current collecting regions.
Titulo: Compositional control of continuously graded anode functional layer

Sentencas: The compositional profile was characterized using energy dispersive X-ray spectroscopic mapping.
Titulo: Compositional control of continuously graded anode functional layer

Sentencas: An analytical model of the compound aerosol deposition was developed.
Titulo: Compositional control of continuously graded anode functional layer

Sentencas: The model predicted compositional profiles for both samples that closely matched the measured profiles, suggesting that aerosol-based deposition methods are capable of creating functional gradation on length scales suitable for solid oxide fuel cell structures.
Titulo: Compositional control of continuously graded anode functional layer

Sentencas: The electrochemical performances of the two cells are analyzed using electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS).
Titulo: Compositional control of continuously graded anode functional layer
